sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as MaaS Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS Terminate
    participant Wasm as Kuadrant Wasm Plugin<br/>(in-process)
    participant Authorino as Authorino<br/>50051/TCP gRPC mTLS
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant ExtProc as payload-processing<br/>9004/TCP gRPC TLS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Backend as Model Backend<br/>(KServe / External)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,Backend: Flow 1: API Key Authentication and Model Inference

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/llama:predict<br/>Authorization: Bearer sk-oai-*<br/>TLS 1.3
    Gateway->>Wasm: Route match → auth check
    Wasm->>Authorino: gRPC auth request<br/>mTLS
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/api-keys/validate<br/>NetworkPolicy protected
    MaaSAPI->>PG: SELECT hash, subscription<br/>SHA-256 constant-time compare
    PG-->>MaaSAPI: API key metadata + subscription
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: 200 OK (user, groups, subscription)
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/subscriptions/select<br/>NetworkPolicy protected
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Selected subscription + rate limit context
    Authorino-->>Wasm: Auth response (identity + metadata)
    Wasm-->>Gateway: Auth OK + rate limit check via Limitador

    Gateway->>ExtProc: ext_proc request body<br/>gRPC TLS SIMPLE :9004
    Note over ExtProc: Plugin pipeline:<br/>1. Extract model → X-Gateway-Model-Name<br/>2. Resolve provider endpoint<br/>3. Translate API format<br/>4. Inject backend credentials
    ExtProc->>K8sAPI: GET Secret (backend API key)<br/>ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>ExtProc: Secret data
    ExtProc-->>Gateway: Modified headers + body<br/>(credential injected, API translated)

    Gateway->>Backend: Proxied request<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Injected API key
    Backend-->>Gateway: Inference response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON response<br/>TLS 1.3

    Note over Client,Backend: Flow 2: Subscription and Policy Lifecycle

    participant Admin as Admin / Platform
    participant Controller as maas-controller

    Admin->>K8sAPI: Create MaaSSubscription CR<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Admin->>K8sAPI: Create MaaSAuthPolicy CR<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Informer notification
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Aggregate → Create AuthPolicy<br/>(per-model, CEL expressions)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Aggregate → Create TokenRateLimitPolicy<br/>(per-model, per-subscription limits)
    K8sAPI-->>Authorino: Kuadrant reconciles AuthPolicy
    Note over Authorino: Auth rules updated<br/>for model routes

    Note over Client,Backend: Flow 3: Tenant Platform Reconcile

    Admin->>K8sAPI: Enable modelsAsService on DSC
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: LifecycleReconciler → Config CR
    Controller->>K8sAPI: TenantReconciler reads Tenant CR
    Note over Controller: Kustomize pipeline:<br/>render → post-render transforms<br/>→ server-side apply
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Apply: Deployment, Service,<br/>HTTPRoute, AuthPolicy,<br/>NetworkPolicy, EnvoyFilter,<br/>DestinationRule, Telemetry, ...
